Logger for testing Trolley Workflow:

cd ~/gr4_ws
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source install/setup.bash
python3 tools/mission_run_logger.py


ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'new_run'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark before_drive_under'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'end_run'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'status'}"



The logger commands are only for the CSV logger. They do not move the robot.

`new_run`
Starts a fresh test run in the CSV. If another run is active, it closes that run first. Use this right before you begin a trolley test.

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'new_run'}"
```

`mark <label>`
Adds a manual note into the event CSV at the current time. Useful for things like “robot looked left”, “operator pressed side_align”, “bad angle”, etc.

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark before_drive_under'}"
```

`end_run`
Ends the active run and writes one row to the summary CSV with total time and milestone times:
approach goal, side align complete, trolley type checked, under trolley, first fine ArUco estimate,
fine align complete, dropoff goal, and drive out.

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'end_run'}"
```

`abort_run`
Also ends the active run, but marks the summary as aborted instead of normal/manual end.

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'abort_run'}"
```

`status`
Prints/publishes where the CSV files are and whether a run is active.

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'status'}"
```

Also: the logger auto-starts a run when it sees `/trolley_command` with `trolley_ready`.
By default it auto-ends when `/dropzone_mission_status` reports `drive_out_done`.
For docking-only tests, send `end_run` after `fine_align_complete`.
